<title>SOUTH AFRICA: UNISPIN 15-MONTHS PROFIT PLUNGES.</title>
<headline>UNISPIN 15-MONTHS PROFIT PLUNGES.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-03-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>15 months to Dec 31 </p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)	 </p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     0.3	   vs 18.0</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   0.90	  vs 10.47</p>
<p>    Operating income	8.65	  vs 26.55</p>
<p>    Finance costs	   7.74	  vs 1.46</p>
<p>    Tax			 nil	   vs 2.19</p>
<p>    Net income		0.90	  vs 24.35</p>
<p>    Turnover		  293.86	vs 258.67</p>
<p>Full name: Unispin Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - South African textiles firm Unispin said that the</p>
<p>comparative figures were for the year to September 30, 1995.</p>
<p>The firm said 1996 was the first year of a three year plan</p>
<p>for recovery and had encountered tough local market conditions.</p>
<p>It added that, though its plan was going well, no significant</p>
<p>improvement in profit was likely before the latter part of the</p>
<p>current year.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
